The following data were derived from table 1 of the bulletin, "Number of
cases reported by country and by animal species affected":
country / cattle / small ruminants / wild / mixed / total
Germany / 624 / 302 / 13 / 14 / 952
France / 7 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 7
The Netherlands / 176 / 250 / 0 / 34 / 460
Belgium / 296 / 399 / 0 / 0 / 695
Luxembourg / 8 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 8
Total 1111 / 951 / 13 / 47 / 2122
The 3 striking characteristics of the 2006 BTV-8 outbreak in north western
Europe were its latitude, the significant involvement of
clinically-affected cattle, and its continuation deep into the winter
season. Explanation(s) to these phenomena, expected to be instrumental in
the preparations for a possible return of the disease during the
summer/fall of 2007, might be sought in the undertaken entomological and
virological studies. Available results are anticipated with interest. - Mod.AS]
